          },
          [_vm._v("#")]
        ),
        _vm._v(" Flexible units of Measure"),
      ]),
      _vm._v(" "),
      _c("p", [
        _vm._v(
          "The instances of stock items being measured in different Units of Measure are common. In\nAkaunt you can define multiple units as per your requirements. It is also possible that an item\ncould be transacted in one or more units of measure, for e.g. Sugar is purchased in tons and sold\nin either kgs or packets. Akaunt allows you to transact in all the three units of measure for the\nsame item. This configuration allows you to maintain stock items in both Main Units as well as\nAlternate Units.\nAkaunt allows creation of compound as well as alternate units for a stock item. You can\ndefine a Compound unit as a relation between of two simple Units, for e.g. create a compound\nunit namely, Ton of 100 kgs. You can view Stock Summary report in Tail Units also (here in this\ncase, kgs)"
        ),
      ]),
      _vm._v(" "),
      _c("h2", { attrs: { id: "flexible-invoicing" } }, [
        _c(
          "a",
          {
            staticClass: "header-anchor",
            attrs: { href: "#flexible-invoicing" },
          },
          [_vm._v("#")]
        ),
        _vm._v(" Flexible Invoicing"),
      ]),
      _vm._v(" "),
      _c("p", [
        _vm._v(
          "In Akaunt, you have flexibility to invoice items or ledger accounts directly to generate sales\ninvoices. The details that you can include or exclude in an invoice is based on the business needs\nfor instance, you may want to print batch number, Manufacturing as well as expiry date, additional\ndescription for items, show discounts on the invoice and so on."
        ),
      ]),
      _vm._v(" "),
      _c("h2", { attrs: { id: "purchase-invoices" } }, [
        _c(
          "a",
          {
            staticClass: "header-anchor",
            attrs: { href: "#purchase-invoices" },
          },
          [_vm._v("#")]
        ),
        _vm._v(" Purchase Invoices"),
      ]),
      _vm._v(" "),
      _c("p", [
        _vm._v(
          "Akaunt provides the option to enter purchase transactions in invoice format and hence\nentering vendor invoices is made easy. When you enter purchase detailw in the invoice format,\nthe stock items selected are automatically updated in the stock summary. You can apportion addi-\ntional expenses, like taxes, freight etc., to stock items which affects their valuations."
        ),
      ]),
      _vm._v(" "),
      _c(
        "h2",
        { attrs: { id: "unlimited-grouping-categorization-of-stock-items" } },
        [
          _c(
            "a",
            {
              staticClass: "header-anchor",
              attrs: {
                href: "#unlimited-grouping-categorization-of-stock-items",
              },
            },
            [_vm._v("#")]
          ),
          _vm._v(" Unlimited Grouping & Categorization of Stock items"),
        ]
      ),
      _vm._v(" "),
      _c("p", [
        _vm._v(
          "Akaunt allows unlimited grouping of stock Items to Stock Groups or subgroups at any point of\ntime. It also allows to categorize stock items based on their specific nature or type or brand in\norder to generate customised inventory reports."
        ),
      ]),
      _vm._v(" "),
      _c("h2", { attrs: { id: "stock-group" } }, [
        _c(
          "a",
          { staticClass: "header-anchor", attrs: { href: "#stock-group" } },
          [_vm._v("#")]
        ),
        _vm._v(" Stock Group"),
      ]),
      _vm._v(" "),
      _c("p", [
        _vm._v(
          "In Akaunt, you can classify all common stock items to a single group, for instance Raw mate-\nrials, Components Consumables, Desktop computers, Scanners etc. Grouping of stock items\nfacilitates effective and substantive reporting on stock items. In Akaunt, you can create\nunlimited levels of groups for in-depth analysis."
        ),
      ]),
      _vm._v(" "),
      _c("h2", { attrs: { id: "stock-category" } }, [
        _c(
          "a",
          { staticClass: "header-anchor", attrs: { href: "#stock-category" } },
          [_vm._v("#")]
        ),
        _vm._v(" Stock Category"),
      ]),
      _vm._v(" "),
      _c("p", [
        _vm._v(
          "In many cases, you may want to classify stock items which are similar in nature but are grouped\nunder different Stock Groups. Akaunt provides you a feature namely, Stock Categories,\nwhich allows parallel classification of stock items to separate categories besides grouping.\nFor example, you may group Television sets of different sizes based on their size viz., TV's of 14\ninches, 21 inches, 29 inches and so on. But however, if you require reports on, which brand sells\nmore. In such cases, you require parallel classification of stock items to stock categories viz.,\nSony, Panasonic, LG, Samsung, Philips, etc.\nIn Akaunt you can create stock items and group under the respective groups and parallely\nclassify them under the respective Stock Categories. You could however, interchange the stock\ncategory or stock group based on your convenience and reporting requirements."
        ),
      ]),
      _vm._v(" "),
      _c("h2", { attrs: { id: "voucher-classes-to-expedite-voucher-entry" } }, [
        _c(
          "a",
          {
            staticClass: "header-anchor",
            attrs: { href: "#voucher-classes-to-expedite-voucher-entry" },
          },
          [_vm._v("#")]
        ),
        _vm._v(" Voucher Classes to expedite voucher Entry"),
      ]),
      _vm._v(" "),
      _c("p", [
        _vm._v(
          "Akaunt provides an option to automate and expedite voucher entry with the help of Voucher\nClasses. You can use this facility for most voucher types (e.g. Payment, Receipt, Sales etc) to\nmake data entry easier and faster. This facility acts as a control, to restrict users from choosing\nany other ledger accounts other than those to which the transaction needs to be posted and\nthereby minimizes errors during data entry."
        ),
      ]),
      _vm._v(" "),
      _c("p", [
        _vm._v(
          "For example, you may create Voucher Class under Receipt Voucher Type to automate Bank\nReceipts or Bank Payments under Payment Voucher Type. You will find the procedure for creating\nvoucher classes for Bank Receipts is the same as that for Bank Payments. The only precaution is\nthat during transactions, you have to enter the details on the credit side only."
        ),
      ]),
      _vm._v(" "),
      _c("h2", { attrs: { id: "voucher-classes-for-sales-invoice" } }, [
        _c(
          "a",
          {
            staticClass: "header-anchor",
            attrs: { href: "#voucher-classes-for-sales-invoice" },
          },
          [_vm._v("#")]
        ),
        _vm._v(" Voucher Classes for Sales Invoice"),
      ]),
      _vm._v(" "),
      _c("p", [
        _vm._v(
          "Voucher classes for invoices can be used to significantly automate ledger entries where tax calcu-\nlations, additional charges, rounding off etc., are involved. You can also specify percentages for\nadditional accounting allocations like taxes, freight and other charges. Based on the values / per-\ncentages entered, the total amount is automatically calculated and prefilled in the respective\nfields."
        ),
      ]),
      _vm._v(" "),
      _c("h2", { attrs: { id: "separate-actual-and-billed-quantities" } }, [
        _c(
          "a",
          {
            staticClass: "header-anchor",
            attrs: { href: "#separate-actual-and-billed-quantities" },
          },
          [_vm._v("#")]
        ),
        _vm._v(" Separate Actual and Billed Quantities"),
      ]),
      _vm._v(" "),
      _c("p", [
        _vm._v(
          "There are situations when you have to invoice the customer for a particular quantity but actually\nsupply a different quantity. Akaunt allows you to handle such situations with the hlep of Use\ndifferent Actual and Billed Qty option. Using this option, you can specify different acutally and\nbilled quantities in the same invoice. The Actual quantity updates the stock balances and Billed\nquantities affect the books of accounts. This feature is widely used to record supply of free items.\nfurther, this option will be useful when you have to supply free item(s) for sale of a fixed number of\ngoods or if you have to supply free samples to your customer."
        ),
      ]),
      _vm._v(" "),
      _c("div", { staticClass: "custom-block tip" }, [
        _c("p", { staticClass: "custom-block-title" }, [_vm._v("TIP")]),
        _vm._v(" "),
        _c("p", [
          _vm._v(
            "The Actual Qty affects the stock balances while the Billed Qty affects only\nthe Books of Accounts."
          ),
        ]),
      ]),
      _vm._v(" "),
      _c("h2", { attrs: { id: "gross-profits-and-consumption-report" } }, [
        _c(
          "a",
          {
            staticClass: "header-anchor",
            attrs: { href: "#gross-profits-and-consumption-report" },
          },
          [_vm._v("#")]
        ),
        _vm._v(" Gross Profits and Consumption Report"),
      ]),
      _vm._v(" "),
      _c("p", [
        _vm._v(
          "Consumption basically means, the quantity / value of materials used (consumed) in the process of\nmanufacturing, selling or written off. Akaunt automatically tracks the movement of materials\nconsumed. You can view the consumption report along with gross profit for every item."
        ),
      ]),
      _vm._v(" "),
      _c("h2", { attrs: { id: "use-stock-item-names-and-or-part-numbers" } }, [
        _c(
          "a",
          {
            staticClass: "header-anchor",
            attrs: { href: "#use-stock-item-names-and-or-part-numbers" },
          },
          [_vm._v("#")]
        ),
        _vm._v(" Use Stock Item Names and / or Part Numbers"),
      ]),
      _vm._v(" "),
      _c("p", [
        _vm._v(
          "Stock items can be created in Akaunt by specifying their actual names as well as by their Part\nNumbers. This makes it convenient for many users dealing in certain industries (like Computer/\nAutomobile Industries) where items are generally identified by their Part Nos. You can also view\nreports for all stock items with their actual names or by part numbers or both."
        ),
      ]),
      _vm._v(" "),
      _c("h2", { attrs: { id: "pos-invoicing" } }, [
        _c(
          "a",
          { staticClass: "header-anchor", attrs: { href: "#pos-invoicing" } },
          [_vm._v("#")]
        ),
        _vm._v(" POS Invoicing"),
      ]),
      _vm._v(" "),
      _c("p", [
        _vm._v(
          "A Point of Sale is either a retail shop, a check-out counter in a shop or any other location where\nsales transactions take place. Akaunt's POS feature is fully integrated with Accounts and\ninventory functions. You can POS Invoice with Cash and Credit/Debit card transactions and effec-\ntively manage gift coupons, vouchers, discount coupons etc.\nThe POS feature in Akaunt enables you to print invoices in continuous or 40 column modes.\nIt automates your data entry and calculations during invoicing. You can also generate standard\nand POS specific reports such as Cash Registers, POS Registers, and Inventory Reports etc."
        ),
      ]),
    ]
  )
}
var staticRenderFns = []
